Dingocoin partnered with ViaBTC, the world's largest Scrypt mining pool, integrating over 1 million miners to earn DINGO rewards. This boosted network security through massive hashpower and announced upcoming support in CoinEx Wallet, positioning Dingocoin as a key player in Scrypt mining revenue and payments.

Dingocoin was added to Komodo Wallet (a non-custodial, multi-asset wallet available on web, mobile, desktop, and more) and Komodo DEX (a decentralized exchange for peer-to-peer trading). This expanded accessibility with no KYC requirements, emphasizing privacy and decentralization. The achievement was credited to community "Guardians" driving the integration.

The Geelong hard fork upgrade was revealed, set to increase transaction throughput from 33 TPS to 330 TPS while maintaining PoW securityâ€”a 10x boost for scalability. September: Geelong Upgrade Live and Multiple Listings/Promotions
The Geelong upgrade successfully activated at block 2,254,540, achieving the 330 TPS milestone with seamless network transition. Node operators and miners were thanked for updating to v1.18.0.0.  

October: Exchange Ops
Dingocoin was listed on https://t.co/StnQ9cq6gs for DINGO/USDT trading, with wrapped versions (wDINGO) on Solana, Polygon, and BSC for cross-chain access, including U.S. users. BitMart ran new-user promotions sharing millions of DINGO rewards for KYC-verified sign-ups. 

November: Positive Momentum from Flip Wallet Partnership
Dingocoin benefited indirectly from NBX's strategic acquisition of 50% stake in Flip Company (behind the Flip non-custodial wallet with 1M+ downloads). Posts celebrated this as a "new era" for hybrid custodial/non-custodial ecosystems, with Dingocoin already integrated into Flip, enhancing its utility in the Nordics and beyond. 

December: Ongoing Building and Community Engagement
Emphasized continued development with posts like "WE KEEP BUILDING!" amid broader crypto celebrations, such as CoinEx's 8th anniversary. Indication in chats about early AMA being prepared with upcoming partnership talks. 

Overall, 2025 was a year of maturation for Dingocoin, with a focus on scalability (via upgrades), security (mining partnerships), and accessibility (listings and wallets). The project maintained its decentralized ethos, with community-driven efforts ("do-ocracy") credited for progress.
